  <div class="project-header">
    'I Remember in Flushes + Flares' (2024)
  </div>

  <!-- INTRO BLOCK -->
  <div class="project-block">
    <p>
      The title comes from the opening line of a poem I wrote, exploring the volatile and fragmented nature of memory. Throughout the photobook, I was drawn to the idea of the unseen. Non-events can sometimes be more moving than what is explicitly knowable. The viewer pieces together an image of someone through fragmented details, as if through flashes of memory. Little, tactile details of people that make up who someone is.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION -->
  <div class="project-section-title">1. Concept</div>

  <div class="project-block">
    <p>
      The lines that overlay the image are inspired by Twombly, whose expressive lines I interpret as the trajectory of one’s life. Since this photo series explores a lost relationship, the lines in this photo represent the evolving dynamics between two people.
    </p>
  </div>

